svg.text: Vivaldi wrote over 500 concertos that's a piece featuring one solo
instrument with a backup orchestra. He composed so quickly that people
said he could write one faster than someone could copy it!
"The Four Seasons" is a set of four pieces one for Spring,
Summer, Autumn, and Winter and Spring is the most famous.
This is a concerto, which means one solo instrument (violin)
shows off while the orchestra backs it up.
Listen for the solo violin imitating birds singing, thunder,
